    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-16T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="390"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/346.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Hartman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-16T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your February 14, 6 p.m. Report by cable what American interests are in danger by
                    revolution which, in your opinion, would receive protection from presence of
                    warship in Ecuadorian waters.</p>
                <p>On account of yellow fever and the unfortunate deaths of Captain Bertolette and
                    two seamen in December, 1911, Department does not desire to send ship unless
                    absolutely necessary. Nearest vessel is <hi rend="italic">Denver</hi> in
                    Nicaragua.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
